---
description: Architecture boundaries, backend/frontend conventions, and quality standards for the curriculum_builder project
alwaysApply: true
---

# Cursor Rules — curriculum_builder

# Architecture boundaries — never cross these
- All prompt strings live exclusively in backend/prompts.py
- All Anthropic API calls are made exclusively in backend/curator.py
- All YouTube API calls are made exclusively in backend/youtube_client.py
- All Pydantic models are defined in backend/models.py
- All config and constants come from backend/config.py via environment variables only
- All frontend API calls go through frontend/src/api/client.js only

# Backend rules
- FastAPI routes must never block the event loop — wrap all SDK calls in asyncio.get_event_loop().run_in_executor()
- SSE routes must send: progress events during processing, a final "result" event with full curriculum JSON, an "error" event on failure
- Always add CORS middleware using CORS_ORIGINS from config.py
- Return {"error": message} with correct HTTP status on all exceptions

# LLM rules
- Log input_tokens and output_tokens to stdout after every Anthropic API call
- Strip markdown code fences before json.loads() on every LLM response
- On JSON parse failure: log the full raw response string at ERROR level, then retry once
- Never retry more than once
- Never make Anthropic API calls outside curator.py

# YouTube rules
- Never invent or mock video data — every VideoCandidate must come from a real API response
- Always make the second videos().list() call for durations and statistics
- Parse ISO 8601 durations with isodate only — no regex or manual math
- Handle quota errors explicitly with a descriptive RuntimeError

# Frontend rules
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes only — loaded via CDN, no npm package
- No chart libraries — the radar chart in EvalDashboard.jsx must be pure SVG
- All fetch/EventSource calls go through frontend/src/api/client.js
- Show a clear error state when the backend is unreachable
- The AgentProgress component must update live as SSE events arrive — do not batch them

# Code quality
- Type hints on every Python function signature and return type
- Docstrings on every Python function and every module
- No bare print() in backend — use logging or Rich
- Prefer explicit over clever in both Python and React
- No untyped useState — always initialize with the correct type (null, [], {}, "")

# Evaluation
- Programmatic metrics (budget, coverage, dedup) must not make LLM calls
- LLM eval metrics must use build_eval_metric_prompt from prompts.py
- Document known blind spots inline in evaluator.py as # BLIND SPOT: comments

# Security
- Never commit .env — only .env.example with empty values
- Never log API keys
- Never expose API keys to the frontend

# Git
- Final commit must be tagged v1-submission
- eval_results/ contents should not be committed except .gitkeep
